{{Infobox saint |name= Abibon |image= |imagesize= |caption= |titles= Saint |birth_date= 1th century |birth_place= |death_date= |death_place= |feast_day= December 2 |venerated_in= Christian church |beatified_date= |beatified_place= |beatified_by= |canonized_date= |canonized_place= |canonized_by= |major_shrine= |attributes= |patronage= |issues= |suppressed_date= |ethnicity= |religion= [[Christianity]] |prayer= }}
'''Abibon''' (fl. 1st century) was the son of [[Gamaliel]], the teacher of [[Paul the Apostle]]. He is said by some sources to have been baptized with his father and his brother Nicodemus. They are regarded as [[saints]] of the Christian church. The finding of their relics was celebrated as a [[feast day]] on August 3, and their [[feast day]]s especially commemorated on December 2 in [[Pisa]].
==References== * Holweck, F. G. ''A Biographical Dictionary of the Saints''. St. Louis, MO: B. Herder Book Co. 1924.
