[[File:Lotus plants at Dazu Lotus Manor.JPG|thumb|[[Nelumbo|Lotus]] plants at Dazu Lotus Manor with traditional-style buildings in the background.]] [[File:Bridge at Dazu Lotus Manor.JPG|thumb|Bridge at Dazu Lotus Manor.]]
'''Dazu Lotus Manor''' (大足荷花山庄) is a [[Nelumbo|lotus]] farm attraction in [[Dazu District|Dazu]], [[Chongqing Municipality]], [[China]].<ref name="mpelembe">{{cite web| url=http://world-news.mpelembe.net/home/china-lotus-exhibition | title=China Lotus Exhibition – Outer-space bred lotus shown at 25th National Lotus Flowers Exhibition in Dazu County, China | publisher=Mpelembe | work=World News | date=10 July 2011 | accessdate=21 September 2014 }}</ref>
The attraction was established in 1992 and is owned by Luo Dengqiang. It covers 33 hectares and is located in [[Baoding Township]], [[Dazu District]]. It is a holiday resort with floral plants on display, especially aquatic species, and other recreational facilities.<ref name="spacedaily">{{cite web| url=http://www.spacedaily.com/news/food-05h.html | title=Farmer Becomes First Chinese Individual To Breed Seeds In Space | publisher=Space Daily | date=26 July 2005 | accessdate=21 September 2014 }}</ref> The site included some reconstructed traditional buildings. It is close to the [[Dazu Rock Carvings]] World Heritage Site.
Seeds of lotus plants on the site have been taken into space, with mutations claimed as a result.<ref name="mpelembe" /><ref name="spacedaily" /><ref>{{cite web| url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=GqXpUivgfeY | title=Mutant Lotus Bred in Space on Display in Chongqing, China | publisher=[[YouTube]] | author=NTDTV | accessdate=21 September 2014 }}</ref> 3,000 seeds were sent into space by the [[Beijing Space Satellite Application Company]].<ref>{{cite web| url=http://english.people.com.cn/200507/25/eng20050725_198120.html | title=Feature: Farmer becomes first Chinese individual to breed seeds in space | website=www.people.com.cn | location=China | date=25 July 2005 | accessdate=21 September 2014 }}</ref> Luo Dengqiang was the first Chinese individual to undertake such a space programme.<ref>{{cite news| url=http://www.terradaily.com/news/food-05h.html | title=Farmer Becomes First Chinese Individual To Breed Seeds In Space | publisher=TerraDaily | website=www.terradaily.com | date=26 July 2005 | accessdate=21 September 2014 }}</ref>
