{{Infobox person | name = Erik Aadahl | birth_name = | birth_date = {{Birth date and age|1976|9|16}} | birth_place = [[San Francisco]], [[California]] | death_date = <!-- {{Death date and age|YYYY|MM|DD|YYYY|MM|DD}} or {{Death-date and age|Month DD, YYYY|Month DD, YYYY}} (death date then birth date) --> | death_place = | nationality = U.S. | other_names = | known_for = | occupation = Sound editor | years_active = 1998-present }} '''Erik Aadahl''' (born September 16, 1976)<ref>State of California. ''California Birth Index, 1905-1995'' (Sacramento, CA: State of California Department of Health Services, Center for Health Statistics), 2005.</ref> is an American sound editor.
He graduated from the [[University of Southern California]]'s School of Cinematic Arts in 1998.<ref>{{cite web|author=Miguel Isaza|title=Erik Aadahl Special:Exclusive Interview|url=http://designingsound.org/2010/03/erik-aadahl-special-exclusive-interview/|publisher=Designingsound.org|date=March 4, 2010|accessdate=May 14, 2012}}</ref> He was supervising sound editor on ''[[Transformers: Dark of the Moon]]'',<ref>{{cite news|title=Sound editor Erik Aadahl: ‘7.1 can heighten 3D experience’|publisher=TVBEurope.com|date=August 1, 2011}}</ref> for which he was nominated for an [[Academy Award]].<ref>{{cite web|author=Jonathan Morales |title=SF State alums nominated for Academy Awards |publisher=[[San Francisco State University]] |url=http://www.sfsu.edu/~news/2012/spring/15.html |date=January 30, 2012 |accessdate=May 14, 2012 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120618233209/http://www.sfsu.edu/~news/2012/spring/15.html |archivedate=June 18, 2012 |df= }}</ref><ref>{{cite news|author=Tommy Brakstad|title=Norsk studentfilm Oscar-nominert|language=Norwegian|trans-title=Norwegian film student nominated for Oscar|url=http://www.vg.no/film/artikkel.php?artid=10076546|date=January 24, 2012|accessdate=May 14, 2012}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|author=|title=84th annual Academy Awards nominees|publisher=[[USA Today]]|url=https://www.usatoday.com/life/movies/movieawards/oscars/story/2012-01-19/Oscar-nominees-list/52765068/1|date=January 24, 2012|accessdate=May 14, 2012}}</ref> Aadahl notably worked on [[Godzilla]]'s "roar" for the 2014 ''[[Godzilla (2014 film)|Godzilla]]'' film and voiced [[Bumblebee (Transformers)|Bumblebee]] in ''[[Transformers: The Last Knight]]''.<ref>{{cite web |publisher=The Motley Fool |url=http://www.fool.com/investing/general/2014/03/02/this-is-the-godzilla-weve-all-been-waiting-for.aspx |title=This is the Godzilla We’ve All Been Waiting For |first= Steve |last=Symington |date=March 2, 2014 |accessdate=March 2, 2014}}</ref>
